  standards_of_creation = 'Structured Decision Making (SDM) tools: Hotline Screening Tool, Safety Assessment, Risk Assessment, Family Strengths and Needs Assessment, Reunification Reassessment; CPS investigation report format (allegation, investigation, findings, disposition — substantiated/inconclusive/unfounded); jurisdiction/disposition report (court-mandated format per CRC 5.690); safety plan documentation (in-home safety plan with specific safety actions, responsible parties, monitoring); case plan (Cal. WIC § 16501.1 — specific goals, objectives, tasks, timeframes, services); visitation schedule documentation; placement documentation (relative/NREFM/foster family agency/group home — placement choice form); CACI reporting (DOJ notification within 36 hours of substantiation per Penal Code § 11169); cross-report documentation (law enforcement, DA, licensing per Penal Code § 11166.3); ICPC-100A (Interstate Compact Placement Request); service referral documentation; Team Decision Making (TDM) meeting notes',
  soc_controls = 'Initial response time compliance (immediate/24-hour/10-day per CDSS SDM Hotline Screening Tool); cross-reporting to law enforcement within 36 hours (Penal Code § 11166(j)); face-to-face contact with child within response timeframe; monthly caseworker visits (42 USC § 624 — federal requirement); CACI notification within 36 hours of substantiation; CACI hearing rights notification to subject (Penal Code § 11169(c)); case plan completion within 60 days of disposition; court report filing deadlines (10 days before hearing per CRC 5.690(b)); relative identification and notification within 30 days of removal (WIC § 309(e)(1)); ICWA inquiry at initial contact; background check compliance for all placements (CLETS, CACI, FBI, DOJ LiveScan); supervised visit scheduling compliance; service referral follow-up tracking; case documentation timeliness (same day for critical events); caseload standards monitoring (CDSS recommended ratios); confidentiality compliance (WIC § 827 — juvenile records)'
